ALWAYS follow these rules strictly. Do not violate under any circumstances.

# App Overview

This is a Tasbeeh (Zikr counter) web application focused on simplicity, spirituality, and distraction-free interaction.

Core features:

- Tasbeeh counter (primary screen)
- Tasbeeh list (multiple zikr items)
- Add/Edit tasbeeh
- Progress tracking (optional future)

---

# Engineering Principles

## Component-Driven Development (CDD)

- Build UI using small, reusable, composable components
- Components must be:
  - Isolated
  - Reusable
  - Testable
- No large monolithic components
- Extract shared UI into common components early

---

# Project Architecture (Scalable & Production-Grade)

Use a feature-based + shared architecture:

src/
app/
providers/
routes/
theme/

features/
tasbeeh/
components/
screens/
store/
types/
utils/

shared/
components/
hooks/
utils/
constants/
locales/
types/

assets/

---

# Folder Rules

- Each folder MUST have barrel exports (`index.ts`)
- No deep relative imports (use absolute imports)
- Group logic by feature, not by type

---

# Routing

- All routes MUST be defined in constants
- No hardcoded route strings
- Use a central route config

Example:
shared/constants/routes.ts

---

# Localization (i18n-ready)

- All user-facing text MUST come from locale files
- No hardcoded strings in components

Structure:
shared/locales/en.ts
shared/locales/index.ts

- Default language: English
- Must be easily extendable to Arabic / Urdu

---

# State Management

Use Zustand for state management.

Rules:

- Store must be feature-based
- No global dumping store
- Keep state minimal and normalized
- Avoid deeply nested objects

Persistence:

- Use localStorage
- Abstract persistence logic (no direct usage in components)

---

# Data Modeling

- Use normalized and flat structures
- Avoid duplication
- Use IDs for referencing
- Keep data structures scalable

---

# Design System (Material UI)

All UI MUST use **:contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}** components.

DO:

- Use MUI components (Box, Stack, Typography, Button, Card)
- Follow MUI composition patterns
- Use theme tokens only

DO NOT:

- Use raw HTML if MUI alternative exists
- Mix UI libraries
- Override styles unnecessarily

---

# Theming (STRICT)

- NO hardcoded colors anywhere in the app
- All colors MUST come from theme

Define:

- Light theme
- Dark theme

Location:

app/theme/

Theme must include:

- palette (primary, secondary, background)
- spacing
- typography
- shape (border radius)

Custom tokens allowed:

theme.custom.\*

---

# Styling Rules

- Prefer `sx` with theme tokens
- No inline hardcoded values like:
  - colors
  - spacing
